Dhanaseelan can you please suggest what is the correct way to configure sanity in Github PR to run the appropriate nxos image type?

def filter_on_time(self, queryset, name, value):
        if value:
            queryset = queryset.filter(created_at__gt=F('job__created_at') + timedelta(hours=int(value)))
        return queryset

That would be nice, but I recently looked this up and all I saw was a way to add a test "configuration" which wasn't entirely well explained. Here's the quote:

XFLOW_GH_OPT:sanity_config:"/ws/asehgal-rtp/sanity/standalone_sanity.json"
Sample json config
[{
"testsuite": "eor_s1_uls",
"system": "uls",
"asic": "eor_s1"
}]

For CDT/ULS sanity, use following format
Sample Config file
[{
"cdt_asic": "wolfridge"
},
{
"testsuite": "pfmdev_xcvr_uls",
"testbed": "pfmdev_xcvr_uls_tb1",
"image": "nxos64-cs",
"system": "uls_utit",
"product": "standalone"
}]

